properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 11 at 3:04PM CST until February 12 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Omaha/Valley NE
properties.description:
...STRONG COLD FRONT BRINGING SNOW AND WIND WEDNESDAY...

.A strong cold will dive through eastern Nebraska and western Iowa
on Wednesday. The front is scheduled into northeast Nebraska mid
Wednesday morning. Snow, possibly mixed with rain initially, and
strong northwest winds gusting to 40 mph, will accompany the front
as it moves southeast. Temperatures in the middle 30s as the
front arrives will cause precipitation to melt initially, with
temperatures falling rapidly into the 20s by early afternoon. This
will likely cause flash freezing of melted precipitation and very
slippery driving conditions. Also, snow and blowing snow with the
strong northwest winds will cause greatly reduced visibilities.

* WHAT...Snow, blowing snow and flash freeze expected. Total snow
accumulations of up to one inch, visibilities of a half mile,
and ice accumulation of a light glaze. Winds gusting as high as
40 mph.

* WHERE...Portions of northeast Nebraska and west central Iowa.

* WHEN...From 9 AM to 6 PM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and reduced
visibilities. The hazardous conditions could impact the evening
commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM TO 6 PM CST WEDNESDAY
